From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: wisemanjr4 <mitsuking2003@gmail.com>
Date: Tue, 24 Mar 2026 15:50:40 +0900
Subject: [PATCH] SuperVertex: Fix NPE in broadcastChanges for non-full chunks
 (RCT)

sectionLightChanged() uses getAvailableChunkNow() which returns proto-
chunks, adding their ChunkHolder to needsChangeBroadcasting. When RCT
light propagation reaches a loading neighbour chunk, tickChunks calls
broadcastChanges(getFullChunkNowUnchecked()) with null -> NPE crash.

Fix: null-check getFullChunkNowUnchecked() and skip non-full chunks.
No players are tracking proto-chunks so broadcasts can be discarded.

diff --git a/src/main/java/net/minecraft/server/level/ServerChunkCache.java b/src/main/java/net/minecraft/server/level/ServerChunkCache.java
index 1ca61785f683d4175cc351ed90d8abb85c3a668f..64f541a9c2d6f9073bd7d1d22922b3e6a441b35a 100644
--- a/src/main/java/net/minecraft/server/level/ServerChunkCache.java
+++ b/src/main/java/net/minecraft/server/level/ServerChunkCache.java
@@ -869,7 +869,13 @@ public class ServerChunkCache extends ChunkSource {
                 ReferenceOpenHashSet<ChunkHolder> copy = this.chunkMap.needsChangeBroadcasting.clone();
                 this.chunkMap.needsChangeBroadcasting.clear();
                 for (ChunkHolder holder : copy) {
-                    holder.broadcastChanges(holder.getFullChunkNowUnchecked()); // LevelChunks are NEVER unloaded
+                    // SuperVertex start - RCT null guard: sectionLightChanged uses getAvailableChunkNow() (returns proto-chunks),
+                    // but getFullChunkNowUnchecked() returns null for non-full chunks. RCT light propagation to
+                    // adjacent loading chunks causes NPE. Skip and discard — no players tracking non-full chunks yet.
+                    LevelChunk fullChunk = holder.getFullChunkNowUnchecked();
+                    if (fullChunk == null) continue;
+                    // SuperVertex end
+                    holder.broadcastChanges(fullChunk); // LevelChunks are NEVER unloaded
                     if (holder.needsBroadcastChanges()) {
                         // I DON'T want to KNOW what DUMB plugins might be doing.
                         this.chunkMap.needsChangeBroadcasting.add(holder);
